Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.57,0:00:03.22,Default,Shop person,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.22,0:00:05.68,Bengoshi-Tavern_Noren,Sign,0,0,0,,Tavern \NYoshi
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.57,0:00:09.85,Default,Person,0,0,0,,Add an order of yakisoba and yakitori.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.31,0:00:12.66,Default,Tomoe,0,0,0,,Did you bring the beer to table two?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.66,0:00:13.99,Default,Tomoe,0,0,0,,The day will end \Nbefore you get it there!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.14,0:00:15.16,Default,Miki,0,0,0,,Yes, I'll do it right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.59,0:00:17.20,Default,Shunsuke,0,0,0,,Table one's yakitori, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.20,0:00:18.06,Default,Miki,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.30,0:00:20.20,Default,Tomoe,0,0,0,,Were you listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.20,0:00:22.17,Default,Tomoe,0,0,0,,I said the beer {\i1}first.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.17,0:00:27.37,Bengoshi-Credits_Miki,Caption left,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,0)}Yoshioka family, bride \NYoshioka Miki
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.17,0:00:27.37,Bengoshi-Credits_Tomoe,Caption right,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,0)}Yoshioka family, mother-in-law \NYoshioka Tomoe
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.59,0:00:25.47,Default,Tomoe,0,0,0,,Go do that first, like I told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.47,0:00:27.37,Default,Tomoe,0,0,0,,What a useless bride!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.50,0:00:28.68,Default,Miki,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.40,0:00:32.07,Default,Miki,0,0,0,,Thank you for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.24,0:00:35.80,Default,K,0,0,0,,So, this is your favorite \Ntavern, Yoshie-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.58,0:00:36.95,Bengoshi-Credits_Kanae,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}Hakamada's Assistant \NNonomura Kanae
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.58,0:00:36.95,Bengoshi-Credits_Yoshie,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}Office landlord \NToyama Yoshie
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.91,0:00:37.29,Default,K,0,0,0,,What do you recommend?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.29,0:00:38.63,Default,K,0,0,0,,Other than the yakitori.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.92,0:00:41.16,Default,K,0,0,0,,Yoshie-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.55,0:00:42.26,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.55,0:00:43.52,Default,K,0,0,0,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.52,0:00:45.91,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.91,0:00:47.38,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Nice place, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.62,0:00:49.79,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Their stews are the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.97,0:00:52.89,Default,Y,0,0,0,,You're drinking Oolong tea at a tavern?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.89,0:00:54.60,Default,K,0,0,0,,I don't drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.76,0:00:57.27,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Jeez, you sound just like Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.43,0:00:59.54,Default,Y,0,0,0,,That man doesn't drink,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.54,0:01:01.57,Default,Y,0,0,0,,doesn't pay the rent...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.57,0:01:04.63,Default,Tomoe,0,0,0,,Landlord, we paid the \Nrent just yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.63,0:01:07.10,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Oh, I wasn't talking about \Nyour place, Yoshi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.51,0:01:09.56,Default,Y,0,0,0,,This restaurant is one of my rentals.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.56,0:01:11.02,Default,K,0,0,0,,Really? Here, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.02,0:01:12.55,Default,Miki,0,0,0,,Here's your yakitori.\NThank you for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.55,0:01:15.48,Default,Tomoe,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry for the wait, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.48,0:01:18.62,Default,Tomoe,0,0,0,,Why are you such a slug? \NThe food'll get cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.84,0:01:21.32,Default,Miki,0,0,0,,You told me to serve \Nthe beer to table two first.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.32,0:01:23.97,Default,Tomoe,0,0,0,,You're blaming me? How rude...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.97,0:01:25.61,Default,Tomoe,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.61,0:01:26.48,Default,Tomoe,0,0,0,,How about I bring
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.48,0:01:29.03,Default,Tomoe,0,0,0,,a stew dish on the house, \Nas a token of our apology.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.03,0:01:30.76,Default,Tomoe,0,0,0,,Come on, get the stew.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.64,0:01:30.76,Bengoshi-Overlap,Miki,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.76,0:01:32.97,Default,Y,0,0,0,,It's not cold at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.97,0:01:36.11,Default,Y,0,0,0,,And I was going to order stew anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.11,0:01:37.80,Default,Y,0,0,0,,so just put it on my tab.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.80,0:01:38.48,Default,Miki,0,0,0,,But—
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.48,0:01:39.36,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.36,0:01:42.07,Default,T,0,0,0,,I just heard. I am so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.84,0:01:45.81,Default,T,0,0,0,,Don't just stand there looking stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.81,0:01:48.46,Default,T,0,0,0,,Clean up this table. Do I have \Nto tell you to do everything?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.46,0:01:49.16,Default,M,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.16,0:01:51.75,Default,T,0,0,0,,I have to tell you to do everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.00,0:01:58.37,Default,Rie,0,0,0,,Nao-kun just bought me this shirt!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.92,0:01:59.43,Bengoshi-Overlap,Naoya,0,0,0,,Are you alright, Rie-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.37,0:01:59.43,Default,M,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.55,0:02:02.14,Default,T,0,0,0,,Sorry, for our bride.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.14,0:02:03.53,Default,T,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.53,0:02:05.30,Default,Rie,0,0,0,,What if it stains?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.30,0:02:07.22,Default,Naoya,0,0,0,,Be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.22,0:02:08.27,Default,M,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.27,0:02:10.04,Default,T,0,0,0,,We will pay to have it laundered.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.04,0:02:11.62,Default,T,0,0,0,,Please come this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.50,0:02:13.61,Default,M,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.61,0:02:15.55,Default,T,0,0,0,,That's enough of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.55,0:02:16.81,Default,T,0,0,0,,Get cleaning! Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.38,0:02:19.45,Default,M,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.82,0:02:26.25,Default,K,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.25,0:02:27.65,Default,M,0,0,0,,I can do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.65,0:02:30.52,Default,M,0,0,0,,If I let a customer do my job,\NMother would get angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.18,0:02:32.47,Default,M,0,0,0,,It's fine, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.64,0:02:35.56,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Your hand is bruised.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.53,0:02:40.81,Default,Y,0,0,0,,You can't go on like this much longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.81,0:02:42.06,Default,Y,0,0,0,,It'll be your death.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.61,0:02:50.74,Bengoshi-Yoshioka_Sign,Sign,0,0,0,,Yoshioka
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.92,0:02:55.33,Default,T,0,0,0,,Do you know how much \Ndry cleaners cost nowadays?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.33,0:02:58.42,Default,T,0,0,0,,Shunsuke can't grill enough yakitori \Nto make up for your losses.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.42,0:03:00.00,Default,M,0,0,0,,I am sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.00,0:03:03.34,Default,T,0,0,0,,Look at this filthy room!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.34,0:03:07.78,Default,T,0,0,0,,Do I have to come home \Nexhausted every day to this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.78,0:03:09.05,Default,T,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.40,0:03:13.32,Default,M,0,0,0,,I had to hurry off this \Nmorning for preparations.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.32,0:03:15.83,Default,T,0,0,0,,Don't talk back. Just clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.91,0:03:21.69,Default,T,0,0,0,,Shunsuke, you must be tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.40,0:03:21.81,Bengoshi-Credits_Shunsuke,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}Yoshioka family, groom \NYoshioka Shunsuke
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.69,0:03:23.84,Default,T,0,0,0,,Why don't you take a bath first?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.59,0:03:25.37,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.21,0:03:27.15,Default,T,0,0,0,,Good job today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.55,0:03:32.42,Default,T,0,0,0,,This place is pig sty.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.42,0:03:36.02,Default,T,0,0,0,,Make it fit for human habitation\N before you go to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.71,0:03:38.69,Default,M,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.52,0:03:44.25,Default,T,0,0,0,,There, at the corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.25,0:03:45.58,Default,T,0,0,0,,There's debris everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.58,0:03:48.65,Default,M,0,0,0,,It's midnight. \N Vacuuming would bother the neighbors.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.65,0:03:51.73,Default,T,0,0,0,,You're full of excuses, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.73,0:03:53.67,Default,T,0,0,0,,Here. Try this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.61,0:03:57.38,Default,T,0,0,0,,I'm taking a bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.07,0:04:00.03,Default,M,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.05,0:04:21.10,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,Mother drained the bath by mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.10,0:04:22.09,Default,M,0,0,0,,Mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.09,0:04:24.25,Default,M,0,0,0,,But I'm always the last to bathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.25,0:04:26.14,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,Of course she wouldn't \Ndo it on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.49,0:04:27.93,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,Don't be so paranoid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.93,0:04:29.59,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,Mother's tired. That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.59,0:04:31.52,Default,M,0,0,0,,I'm tired, too, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.52,0:04:34.27,Default,M,0,0,0,,I work just as hard \Nas you and your mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.27,0:04:36.18,Default,M,0,0,0,,but she makes me do more \Nchores when we get home.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.52,0:04:38.77,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,You once said, "I'll endure anything
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.77,0:04:42.77,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,if I can always be with you, Shun-chan."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.77,0:04:45.24,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,You knew you were going \Nto help at the tavern,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.24,0:04:46.98,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,and that we were going to \Nlive with my mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.98,0:04:49.39,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,from before we got married.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.40,0:04:51.48,Default,M,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.48,0:04:54.76,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,Give me a break. I'm tired, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.06,0:04:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.04,0:05:07.51,Bengoshi-Hakamada_Window_Sign,Sign,0,0,0,,Hakamada Law Office
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.51,0:05:06.80,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.07,0:05:10.35,Default,M,0,0,0,,I don't really want to \Ngo to a law office...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.21,0:05:16.88,Bengoshi-Hakamada_Wood_Sign,Plaque,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,0)}Hakamada\N Law Office
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.72,0:05:13.83,Default,Y,0,0,0,,This place is actually\N my friend's bakery.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.83,0:05:14.98,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.23,0:05:19.75,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Sensei, I'm borrowing \Nyour place for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.05,0:05:23.39,Default,Y,0,0,0,,You'll go crazy if you \Nlet that mother-in-law
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.39,0:05:24.87,Default,Y,0,0,0,,keep bullying you like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.87,0:05:27.65,Default,M,0,0,0,,But, I have no intention \Nof leaving my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.65,0:05:29.11,Default,K,0,0,0,,You're from the tavern.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.11,0:05:30.48,Default,K,0,0,0,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.00,0:05:33.40,Bengoshi-Credits_Rina,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}Temp \NShinozuka Rina
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.48,0:05:31.90,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,Tavern?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.25,0:05:34.61,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,Oh, the one Yoshie-san \Ngoes to all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.61,0:05:37.81,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Let's try and think of a solution \Nto your problem together.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.54,0:05:40.86,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Hey, Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.86,0:05:42.84,Default,Y,0,0,0,,You're making too much \Nnoise with that dough.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.84,0:05:46.21,Bengoshi-Credits,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}Attorney \NHakamada Yukio
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.84,0:05:46.87,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,Well, I'm infusing the dough\N with feelings of gratitude to you all...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.14,0:05:49.00,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,and in looking forward to spring,\N I have named this bread "The Special Spring—"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.00,0:05:50.84,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,We don't need to know the name.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.35,0:05:53.28,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Never mind the gratitude\N or the bread!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.28,0:05:54.60,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Pay the rent!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.60,0:05:56.42,Default,K,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry you have to \Nsee all this ugliness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.42,0:05:59.72,Default,M,0,0,0,,I told everyone I was just\Ngoing shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.72,0:06:01.13,Default,M,0,0,0,,I have to get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.12,0:06:03.48,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.85,0:06:05.65,Default,K,0,0,0,,You got really pale!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.86,0:06:08.67,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Miki-san, take a little break here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.79,0:06:09.72,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Sensei, tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.72,0:06:10.72,Default,H,0,0,0,,Oh. Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.72,0:06:11.91,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.54,0:06:14.88,Default,H,0,0,0,,It's ginger tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.88,0:06:17.05,Default,Y,0,0,0,,This is Yoshioka Miki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.05,0:06:21.38,Default,Y,0,0,0,,She's the bride at my favorite \Nhaunt, the Tavern Yoshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.52,0:06:25.01,Default,Y,0,0,0,,I've been noticing it lately,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.01,0:06:28.31,Default,Y,0,0,0,,but her mother-in-law bullies \Nher something terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.31,0:06:30.41,Default,K,0,0,0,,I saw it for myself last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.41,0:06:31.29,Default,K,0,0,0,,It was terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.29,0:06:33.49,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,You look very tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.64,0:06:37.60,Default,H,0,0,0,,By the way, how long did \Nyou sleep last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.36,0:06:40.33,Default,M,0,0,0,,About four hours, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.33,0:06:41.58,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,Four hours?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.70,0:06:43.66,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,It's like you're in cram school.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.66,0:06:46.37,Default,M,0,0,0,,I go in for prep at six in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.69,0:06:48.41,Default,M,0,0,0,,Then, I get the tables set up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.89,0:06:50.78,Default,M,0,0,0,,At night I do all the cleaning,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.78,0:06:53.71,Default,M,0,0,0,,and by the time I get home \Nit's close to one o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.06,0:06:57.01,Default,M,0,0,0,,Then, I have to do chores.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.24,0:06:59.50,Default,M,0,0,0,,So I can't sleep more \Nthan that each night.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.50,0:07:02.36,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,Sleep deprivation is bad for your skin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.31,0:07:04.89,Default,H,0,0,0,,What about your meals?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.89,0:07:06.26,Default,H,0,0,0,,Are you eating properly?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.49,0:07:09.43,Default,M,0,0,0,,Between chores and \Nworking at the tavern,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.76,0:07:12.40,Default,M,0,0,0,,I'm too busy to eat sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.62,0:07:17.13,Default,M,0,0,0,,Often I don't have time to sit \Nand eat lunch or dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.13,0:07:18.08,Default,Y,0,0,0,,That's not good!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.08,0:07:20.15,Default,Y,0,0,0,,You have to eat properly!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.15,0:07:22.01,Default,K,0,0,0,,You don't look well at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.01,0:07:25.43,Default,K,0,0,0,,Why don't you ask your \Nmother-in-law for a day off today?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.31,0:07:29.21,Default,M,0,0,0,,I once had a fever of 104 degrees,\Nand she still made me work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.42,0:07:31.23,Bengoshi-Flashback,T,0,0,0,,Come on. Get on with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.23,0:07:32.68,Bengoshi-Flashback,T,0,0,0,,Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.95,0:07:34.82,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,That's like an underground sweatshop.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.82,0:07:36.99,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Sensei, do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.99,0:07:40.77,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Miki-san will die if she \Ncontinues like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.29,0:07:43.81,Default,H,0,0,0,,Pardon me if I may ask, Miki-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.81,0:07:44.99,Default,H,0,0,0,,but what do you want to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.00,0:07:47.69,Default,M,0,0,0,,I don't want to separate \Nfrom Shun-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.91,0:07:51.97,Default,M,0,0,0,,that is, my husband,\N no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.74,0:07:53.82,Default,M,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.24,0:07:56.47,Default,M,0,0,0,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.46,0:07:58.67,Default,H,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.51,0:08:00.78,Default,K,0,0,0,,Miki-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.78,0:08:06.03,Default,M,0,0,0,,Shun-chan was my upperclassman in\N high school, and I admired him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.99,0:08:08.82,Default,M,0,0,0,,He had a girlfriend for a long time,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.83,0:08:12.28,Default,M,0,0,0,,so I gave up on him for a while...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.28,0:08:15.69,Default,M,0,0,0,,But, after graduation, \Nhe told me they'd broken up...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.02,0:08:17.97,Default,M,0,0,0,,So I aggressively pursued him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.95,0:08:22.33,Default,M,0,0,0,,And we finally got married \Nseven years ago, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.27,0:08:24.93,Default,M,0,0,0,,it was like a dream come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.05,0:08:29.12,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,She's taking advantage \Nof your love for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.12,0:08:30.17,Default,K,0,0,0,,Can't something be done about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.39,0:08:33.51,Default,K,0,0,0,,Like asking your husband to have your \Nmother-in-law live elsewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.01,0:08:37.18,Default,M,0,0,0,,I agreed before we were married \Nthat she would live with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.30,0:08:42.52,Default,M,0,0,0,,Seriously, I have to get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.52,0:08:43.97,Default,M,0,0,0,,Thank you for the tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.97,0:08:45.30,Default,M,0,0,0,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.58,0:08:47.05,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Oh. Miki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.25,0:08:49.09,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Wait—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.29,0:08:53.91,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Jeez...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.61,0:08:57.69,Default,Y,0,0,0,,What a spineless husband, \N not standing up for his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.10,0:09:00.55,Default,Y,0,0,0,,She should dump him \Nand sue for compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.55,0:09:01.93,Default,K,0,0,0,,Yoshie-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.93,0:09:03.79,Default,K,0,0,0,,you have to consider \NMiki-san's feelings, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.79,0:09:06.94,Default,K,0,0,0,,You can't casually make \Ndrastic decisions for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.19,0:09:09.03,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Then, let me ask you, Kanae-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.03,0:09:12.01,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Are you going to do nothing \Nwhile you watch Miki-san slowly die?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.01,0:09:13.74,Default,K,0,0,0,,That's {\i1}not{\i0} what I meant!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.74,0:09:16.21,Default,H,0,0,0,,Please, both of you calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.21,0:09:18.66,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Then {\i1}you'd{\i0} better do something, Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.65,0:09:22.72,Default,H,0,0,0,,I have to respect her decision \Nto stay with her husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.98,0:09:26.49,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,What about suing the \Nmother-in-law for bullying, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.71,0:09:27.14,Default,K,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.14,0:09:28.21,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.44,0:09:29.43,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Let's do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.65,0:09:32.46,Default,H,0,0,0,,Unless circumstances \Nare quite extreme...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.46,0:09:36.60,Default,H,0,0,0,,it's difficult for a daughter-in-law \Nto sue her mother-in-law.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.76,0:09:39.22,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Who cares if it's difficult?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.22,0:09:40.67,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Hurry up and get the ball rolling!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.67,0:09:41.84,Default,K,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.98,0:09:44.12,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.12,0:09:45.08,Default,K,0,0,0,,Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.47,0:09:48.74,Default,H,0,0,0,,Don't move in... so close...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.68,0:09:58.78,Bengoshi-Title,Title,0,0,0,,Divorce Chaser\N{\fs25}~Let's Turn Your Tears into Money~
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.12,0:10:03.96,Bengoshi-Ep_Title,Caption,0,0,0,,Divorce Chaser Episode 10 \NPut an End to the War of In-Laws!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.83,0:10:08.27,Bengoshi-Closed_Today,Sign at door,0,0,0,,Closed Today
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.38,0:10:11.43,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,Why are you cleaning \Nso vigorously today?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.43,0:10:17.25,Default,M,0,0,0,,Because Mother will gripe \Nat me if it's not clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.25,0:10:19.75,Default,M,0,0,0,,Maybe that's not all\N there is to it, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.90,0:10:25.60,Default,M,0,0,0,,Mother doesn't approve of \Nanything I do, regardless.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.03,0:10:29.01,Default,M,0,0,0,,It's futile for me \Nto try to please her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.23,0:10:30.76,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.02,0:10:35.46,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,All you ever do is complain lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.68,0:10:38.09,Default,M,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.09,0:10:39.80,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,Try to get along with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.42,0:10:44.80,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,It's hardest on me when you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.36,0:10:59.61,Default,Yuriko,0,0,0,,Mother, how is the seasoning?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.03,0:11:01.91,Default,Yuriko,0,0,0,,It's hot, so be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.05,0:11:06.02,Default,T,0,0,0,,Mm, what refined seasoning!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.41,0:11:08.40,Default,T,0,0,0,,It's delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.18,0:11:08.40,Bengoshi-Overlap,Shun,0,0,0,,Yuri-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.40,0:11:09.26,Default,M,0,0,0,,Yuri-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.17,0:11:15.52,Default,T,0,0,0,,This young lady is Kubo Yuriko-chan.\N She and Shunsuke are childhood friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.76,0:11:18.20,Bengoshi-Credits_Yuriko,Caption,0,0,0,,Shunsuke's childhood friend\N Kubo Yuriko
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.85,0:11:17.29,Bengoshi-Top,M,0,0,0,,And here's the bride, Miki.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.35,0:11:19.28,Bengoshi-Top,Y,0,0,0,,How do you do? I'm Yuriko.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.85,0:11:21.97,Default,M,0,0,0,,I'm Miki.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.14,0:11:24.01,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Well, I'd better get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.01,0:11:25.42,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Thank you for lending me this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.42,0:11:26.53,Default,T,0,0,0,,You're leaving already?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.53,0:11:28.03,Default,T,0,0,0,,I haven't seen you in so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.03,0:11:29.08,Default,T,0,0,0,,Oh, Shunsuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.08,0:11:31.35,Default,T,0,0,0,,Yuriko-chan brought \Nus fresh red snapper.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.35,0:11:34.01,Default,T,0,0,0,,We cooked it together, didn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.01,0:11:35.70,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Mother invited me the other day,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.70,0:11:37.81,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,so I thought I'd drop in.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.81,0:11:40.87,Default,T,0,0,0,,It's so fun spending time \Nwith you, Yuri-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.87,0:11:42.81,Default,T,0,0,0,,Hey, why don't you stay for dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.81,0:11:45.72,Default,T,0,0,0,,Can you? You can show \Nme your cooking skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.24,0:11:51.10,Default,M,0,0,0,,What a feast.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.10,0:11:52.77,Default,M,0,0,0,,It's like a celebration or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.77,0:11:54.31,Default,T,0,0,0,,Never mind the comments.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.52,0:11:56.42,Default,T,0,0,0,,You're always in my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.69,0:12:02.41,Default,T,0,0,0,,Mm, delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.54,0:12:08.86,Default,T,0,0,0,,All I ever have to eat is \Nhalf-baked swill around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.86,0:12:10.78,Default,T,0,0,0,,This has brought me back to life!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.78,0:12:12.12,Default,T,0,0,0,,Shunsuke, eat up while you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.43,0:12:14.54,Default,T,0,0,0,,It's all your favorites.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.82,0:12:17.41,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,It's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.74,0:12:19.53,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,Your cooking's gotten \Neven better, Yuri-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.12,0:12:21.83,Default,T,0,0,0,,You.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.83,0:12:23.70,Default,T,0,0,0,,You should try it, too, \Nfor future reference.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.77,0:12:26.08,Default,M,0,0,0,,I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.76,0:12:33.34,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.54,0:12:34.97,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Does it meet with your approval?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.59,0:12:36.54,Default,M,0,0,0,,It's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.54,0:12:39.91,Default,T,0,0,0,,Well, so she does know the \Ndifference between good and bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.22,0:12:41.85,Default,T,0,0,0,,She's so bad at cooking,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.85,0:12:43.46,Default,T,0,0,0,,I thought she didn't \Nknow the difference!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.46,0:12:44.70,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,That's terrible, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.70,0:12:46.76,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Of course she knows the difference!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.02,0:12:53.77,Bengoshi-Flashback,Shun,0,0,0,,Try to get along with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.77,0:12:58.20,Bengoshi-Flashback,Shun,0,0,0,,It's hardest on me when you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.90,0:13:05.93,Default,M,0,0,0,,Oh, Mother, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.93,0:13:07.38,Default,M,0,0,0,,Always kidding around.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.38,0:13:08.91,Default,T,0,0,0,,Truth be told,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.91,0:13:13.25,Default,T,0,0,0,,I wanted Shunsuke to marry \Nsomeone like you, Yuri-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.25,0:13:15.35,Default,T,0,0,0,,We have the same \Ntaste in food, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.64,0:13:17.89,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,There's nothing I could do, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.89,0:13:21.82,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,Yuri-chan was already \Nin an arranged marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.82,0:13:23.58,Default,Y,0,0,0,,I was too young, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.58,0:13:24.72,Default,Y,0,0,0,,But it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.11,0:13:27.63,Default,Y,0,0,0,,You got to marry this lovely girl instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.35,0:13:30.51,Default,M,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.24,0:13:35.21,Default,M,0,0,0,,Yuriko-san, how long ago \Ndid you get married?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.29,0:13:36.68,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Let me see...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.68,0:13:38.07,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,seven years ago, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.80,0:13:41.49,Default,M,0,0,0,,Seven years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.49,0:13:45.24,Default,T,0,0,0,,Yuri-chan, you haven't changed a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.24,0:13:47.31,Default,T,0,0,0,,You look ten years younger.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.31,0:13:49.95,Default,T,0,0,0,,She's always been so pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.66,0:13:54.90,Default,T,0,0,0,,And compared to this...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.07,0:14:08.97,Default,T,0,0,0,,You shouldn't sit next to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.09,0:14:12.43,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Mother, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.42,0:14:22.81,Default,T,0,0,0,,Delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.15,0:14:32.03,Default,M,0,0,0,,I can't help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.06,0:14:34.52,Default,M,0,0,0,,I'd like to make myself pretty, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.35,0:14:37.83,Default,M,0,0,0,,but I'm always exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.21,0:14:39.66,Default,M,0,0,0,,I don't even have time to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.66,0:14:43.26,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,Hey, Mother was just kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.39,0:14:45.90,Default,M,0,0,0,,I do everything Mother tells me to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.90,0:14:47.47,Default,M,0,0,0,,at home and at the tavern,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.47,0:14:50.64,Default,M,0,0,0,,to the best of my ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.33,0:14:54.12,Default,T,0,0,0,,Oh, please, listen to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.12,0:14:57.29,Default,T,0,0,0,,You make it sound like I'm forcing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.71,0:15:00.01,Default,T,0,0,0,,You see how rude she is?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.01,0:15:01.92,Default,T,0,0,0,,Right? I'm sick of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.56,0:15:04.75,Default,M,0,0,0,,I'm not your slave, Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.69,0:15:06.52,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,Miki!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.35,0:15:09.09,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,You can't talk like that to Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.43,0:15:10.54,Default,M,0,0,0,,Shun-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.54,0:15:11.96,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,Apologize to her!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.75,0:15:19.14,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Miki-san, don't be so angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.14,0:15:20.80,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Let's all enjoy a friendly meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.05,0:15:22.38,Default,M,0,0,0,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.80,0:15:27.21,Default,M,0,0,0,,What do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.68,0:15:29.61,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.57,0:15:31.67,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,Miki!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.48,0:15:34.43,Default,T,0,0,0,,Let her be!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.95,0:15:36.95,Bengoshi-Hakamada_Window_Sign2,Sign,0,0,0,,Hakamada Law Office
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.73,0:15:41.32,Default,H,0,0,0,,I made chamomile tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.77,0:15:43.31,Default,H,0,0,0,,It's very soothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.22,0:15:48.68,Default,M,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.66,0:15:56.58,Default,Y,0,0,0,,So, this so-called \Nchildhood friend, Yuriko...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.58,0:16:01.31,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Was she  your husband's girlfriend in high school?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.37,0:16:08.40,Default,M,0,0,0,,Shun-chan said that seven years ago,\N before we got married...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.07,0:16:15.11,Default,M,0,0,0,,that his longstanding girlfriend's \Nparents arranged her marriage...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.41,0:16:17.00,Default,M,0,0,0,,and she dumped him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.00,0:16:22.59,Default,K,0,0,0,,But, why did your mother-in-law\N invite his ex-girlfriend to the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.75,0:16:27.93,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,I assume she's been married \Nthe past seven years, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.51,0:16:29.97,Default,M,0,0,0,,Mother is spiteful.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.32,0:16:33.17,Default,M,0,0,0,,She praised Yuriko-san's \Ncooking in front of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.17,0:16:35.54,Default,M,0,0,0,,She compared my looks \Nto hers and laughed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.54,0:16:39.14,Default,M,0,0,0,,She even said she'd wanted \NYuriko-san to marry her son.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.54,0:16:41.60,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Are you kidding?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.60,0:16:44.35,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Isn't the one working\N her fingers to the bone
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.35,0:16:45.35,Default,Y,0,0,0,,you, Miki-san?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.60,0:16:47.13,Default,Y,0,0,0,,How can you be expected
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.13,0:16:50.57,Default,Y,0,0,0,,to cook anything spectacular \Nwhen you have no time?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.57,0:16:52.64,Default,Y,0,0,0,,This is an outrage!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.21,0:16:55.22,Default,K,0,0,0,,And your husband...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.22,0:16:57.26,Default,K,0,0,0,,Did he just quietly watch \Nall that happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.81,0:17:00.33,Default,M,0,0,0,,"You can't talk like that to mother."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.69,0:17:04.75,Default,M,0,0,0,,That's what Shun-chan said \Nwhen I talked back to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.98,0:17:06.47,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,That's awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.82,0:17:08.82,Default,M,0,0,0,,I've reached my limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.93,0:17:10.69,Default,M,0,0,0,,At this rate,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.69,0:17:13.03,Default,M,0,0,0,,I'll gradually turn into \Na horrible person.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.62,0:17:18.13,Default,M,0,0,0,,I've endured this much because\N I love Shun-chan, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.89,0:17:22.05,Default,M,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.00,0:17:24.39,Default,M,0,0,0,,am going to divorce him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.80,0:17:26.76,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.32,0:17:28.70,Default,H,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.87,0:17:31.59,Default,H,0,0,0,,You are officially my client.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.09,0:17:35.35,Default,H,0,0,0,,She overdid it by inviting \Nhis ex-girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.23,0:17:37.77,Default,H,0,0,0,,Let's get ready for the divorce.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.54,0:17:41.30,Default,H,0,0,0,,Let's sue the mother-in-law \Nfor compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.62,0:17:42.65,Default,M,0,0,0,,Compensation?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.07,0:17:46.75,Default,Y,0,0,0,,You're young, so you probably think \Nyou don't need compensation...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.05,0:17:50.38,Default,Y,0,0,0,,but you can't let people \Nwalk all over you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.18,0:17:54.19,Default,H,0,0,0,,From everything I've heard so far,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.19,0:17:57.94,Default,H,0,0,0,,the situation sounds like more\N than just a case of bullying.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.21,0:17:59.57,Default,Y,0,0,0,,How so?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.57,0:18:00.72,Default,K,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.10,0:18:02.43,Default,H,0,0,0,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.43,0:18:04.53,Default,H,0,0,0,,there's something more behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.68,0:18:11.85,Default,H,0,0,0,,Firstly, you must gather \Nevidence of bullying.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.44,0:18:15.37,Default,H,0,0,0,,So, provisionally, please \Napologize to your mother-in-law,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.37,0:18:16.70,Default,H,0,0,0,,and go back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.06,0:18:18.25,Default,M,0,0,0,,Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.89,0:18:20.41,Default,M,0,0,0,,I am sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.92,0:18:23.94,Default,T,0,0,0,,You think an apology is enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.03,0:18:35.22,Default,K,0,0,0,,I think we did the\N right thing. Don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.69,0:18:40.61,Default,Y,0,0,0,,There are times people have \Nto stand up for themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.79,0:18:42.05,Default,Y,0,0,0,,even if it's hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.58,0:18:46.96,Default,K,0,0,0,,You've been worried about \NMiki-san for quite a while now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.20,0:18:49.48,Default,Y,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.01,0:18:51.37,Default,Y,0,0,0,,have a daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.80,0:18:53.07,Default,K,0,0,0,,You have a daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.48,0:18:56.26,Default,Y,0,0,0,,About seven or eight years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.70,0:19:00.06,Default,Y,0,0,0,,my daughter was in the \Nsame situation as Miki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.35,0:19:03.64,Default,Y,0,0,0,,She was bullied constantly by her \NOedipus-complex husband and his mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.97,0:19:06.23,Default,Y,0,0,0,,And she ran away from them,\N leaving all her belongings behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.87,0:19:09.91,Default,Y,0,0,0,,It was Sensei who helped her, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.34,0:19:11.70,Default,Y,0,0,0,,She received compensation...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.70,0:19:13.11,Default,Y,0,0,0,,She got her divorce...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.77,0:19:19.90,Default,Y,0,0,0,,That's why I still rent the office \Nout to that penniless lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.67,0:19:22.43,Default,K,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.65,0:19:26.92,Default,Y,0,0,0,,That's why I had to do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.20,0:19:28.47,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Something for Miki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.68,0:19:38.48,Default,Beer drinkers,0,0,0,,Cheers!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.48,0:19:40.62,Default,M,0,0,0,,Ladies of the Shopping District \NWomen's Association,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.62,0:19:42.51,Default,M,0,0,0,,thank you for your continued patronage.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.51,0:19:45.30,Default,Lady1,0,0,0,,We're celebrating our \Nnewest member today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.54,0:19:48.33,Default,Lady2,0,0,0,,Wow, you really guzzled that beer!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.33,0:19:49.56,Default,Lady3,0,0,0,,How impressive!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.56,0:19:51.22,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Oh, please! I'm shy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.64,0:19:55.25,Default,M,0,0,0,,May I take your order?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.25,0:19:58.46,Default,Lady4,0,0,0,,Miki-san, don't bully your \Nmother-in-law too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.46,0:19:59.07,Default,M,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.07,0:20:02.31,Bengoshi-Credits_Kurumi,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,0)}Freelance Investigator \NUmemoto Kurumi
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.07,0:20:02.31,Bengoshi-Top,Lady,0,0,0,,You haven't attended \Nour meetings lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.31,0:20:04.53,Default,M,0,0,0,,Because my mother-in-law \Nsays I don't need to—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.53,0:20:07.04,Default,T,0,0,0,,Miki-chan, good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.04,0:20:07.92,Default,T,0,0,0,,You must be tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.92,0:20:09.48,Default,T,0,0,0,,You can take a break now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.48,0:20:10.18,Default,M,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.18,0:20:11.44,Default,T,0,0,0,,Good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.44,0:20:13.19,Default,T,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.73,0:20:15.61,Default,T,0,0,0,,She's what you call a monster bride.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.61,0:20:17.60,Default,T,0,0,0,,When she gets in one of her moods,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.60,0:20:20.18,Default,T,0,0,0,,she complains that she's tired, \Nshe yells at everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.18,0:20:22.04,Default,Lady,0,0,0,,That's so scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.04,0:20:24.18,Default,Lady,0,0,0,,You must be careful \Nto never become like her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.18,0:20:25.51,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I'll be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.51,0:20:27.99,Default,T,0,0,0,,I'll bring you some edamame.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.34,0:20:30.29,Default,T,0,0,0,,On the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.63,0:20:32.80,Default,Lady,0,0,0,,You're always so good to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.17,0:20:34.37,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.37,0:20:38.26,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,when did Miki-san stop coming\N to the meetings?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.26,0:20:39.61,Default,Lady,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.61,0:20:41.72,Default,Lady,0,0,0,,It's been three years, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.29,0:20:43.64,Default,Lady,0,0,0,,Speaking of which...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.64,0:20:45.69,Default,Lady,0,0,0,,I think that's when it all began.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.69,0:20:49.88,Default,Lady,0,0,0,,That's when her relationship \Nwith her mother-in-law started to sour.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.88,0:20:51.13,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Three years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.13,0:20:52.14,Default,Lady2,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.14,0:20:56.28,Default,Lady2,0,0,0,,That was about the time she started \Ntalking trash about her daughter-in-law.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.28,0:20:58.03,Default,Lady3,0,0,0,,I think it's quite complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.60,0:21:02.33,Default,T,0,0,0,,Hey, you, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.33,0:21:05.04,Default,T,0,0,0,,I told them I'm giving \Nthem free edamame.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.04,0:21:06.43,Default,T,0,0,0,,Why didn't you have it ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.43,0:21:08.01,Default,M,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. I'll get on it right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.01,0:21:09.30,Default,T,0,0,0,,Just forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.07,0:21:14.20,Default,T,0,0,0,,What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.20,0:21:15.19,Default,M,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.19,0:21:17.60,Default,T,0,0,0,,"I'm sorry.I'm sorry."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.60,0:21:19.05,Default,T,0,0,0,,You think can get away with \Nanything by apologizing!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.05,0:21:20.27,Default,M,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.93,0:21:23.29,Default,T,0,0,0,,Too bad I can't get rid of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.17,0:21:26.72,Default,M,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.06,0:21:31.26,Bengoshi-Hakamada_Window_Sign2,Sign,0,0,0,,Hakamada Law Office
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.63,0:21:34.82,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,She's been bullied like that \Nfor three whole years!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.45,0:21:42.14,Default,H,0,0,0,,For three years...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.81,0:21:46.05,Default,H,0,0,0,,Three years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.05,0:21:47.84,Default,H,0,0,0,,did something happen\N between you and the mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.16,0:21:51.35,Default,H,0,0,0,,There was, wasn't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.18,0:21:54.26,Default,M,0,0,0,,It wasn't about Mother, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.71,0:21:56.00,Default,H,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.91,0:21:58.67,Default,M,0,0,0,,Three years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.07,0:22:01.09,Default,M,0,0,0,,Shu-chan cheated on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.56,0:22:03.59,Default,M,0,0,0,,It was cold then,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.59,0:22:05.86,Default,M,0,0,0,,so I think it was around \Nthe same time of year.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.24,0:22:07.85,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Cheating?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.85,0:22:09.33,Default,Y,0,0,0,,With who?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.14,0:22:11.85,Default,M,0,0,0,,I don't know who it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.74,0:22:14.15,Default,M,0,0,0,,When I questioned him,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.15,0:22:15.76,Default,M,0,0,0,,he turned it around and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.57,0:22:18.37,Default,M,0,0,0,,"Let's get a divorce, then."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.78,0:22:20.84,Default,M,0,0,0,,But, I didn't want a divorce.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.84,0:22:23.88,Default,M,0,0,0,,I said, "I love you, Shun-chan. \NI'll never divorce you."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.26,0:22:26.62,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,The guilty spouse, \Nor more accurately,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.62,0:22:29.86,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,the husband who had an illicit affair \Nwhich could destroy the household,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.65,0:22:38.39,Bengoshi-Vocab_Definition1,Caption white,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,0)}The party guilty of an illicit affair
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.86,0:22:31.88,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,has no legal standing \Nto ask for a divorce.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.98,0:22:38.39,Bengoshi-Vocab_Definition2,Caption red,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,0)}has no standing to demand a divorce.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.49,0:22:33.67,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,If he still insists on a divorce,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.67,0:22:35.92,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,he'd be liable for a \Nhefty compensation fee.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.44,0:22:38.39,Bengoshi-Top,K,0,0,0,,And what did your husband say?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.57,0:22:40.64,Default,M,0,0,0,,He said, "I'm not seeing her any more."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.93,0:22:43.13,Default,M,0,0,0,,Shu-chan was very upfront about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.37,0:22:47.86,Default,K,0,0,0,,Sensei, is there a connection between \Nthe affair three years ago and the bullying?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.31,0:22:53.01,Default,H,0,0,0,,The mother-in-law told her she didn't \Nhave to attend the meetings any more...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.72,0:22:56.54,Default,H,0,0,0,,Kurumi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.91,0:23:02.01,Bengoshi-Closed_Today,Sign at door,0,0,0,,Closed today
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.51,0:23:02.01,Default,Kobayashi,0,0,0,,The rest, I'll leave in your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.12,0:23:04.45,Default,Kobayashi,0,0,0,,That's our meeting for today.\N Good job, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.45,0:23:06.51,Default,All,0,0,0,,Good work!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.51,0:23:10.02,Default,Tomoe,0,0,0,,Good work, everyone. Please, \Nhave some beer on the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.08,0:23:13.32,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,I'm going out for a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.32,0:23:14.72,Default,T,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.46,0:23:19.07,Default,T,0,0,0,,Chairman, good job today.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.07,0:23:20.41,Default,Kobayashi,0,0,0,,Thank you, Madam.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.41,0:23:22.11,Default,Kobayashi,0,0,0,,I always look forward to \Nhaving our meetings at Yoshi,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.11,0:23:23.68,Default,Kobayashi,0,0,0,,especially this part.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.68,0:23:26.84,Default,T,0,0,0,,Thank you for your\N continued support.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.84,0:23:29.20,Default,T,0,0,0,,This is about all I can \Ndo for you, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.20,0:23:32.45,Default,Kobayashi,0,0,0,,By the way, I got you an estimate \Nfor renovating the tavern.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.45,0:23:34.29,Default,T,0,0,0,,Oh, thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.42,0:23:38.30,Default,T,0,0,0,,I can always rely on \NKobayashi Building Contractors.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.30,0:23:39.83,Default,Kobayashi,0,0,0,,We're working on the blueprint.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.30,0:23:42.67,Bengoshi-Credits_Hiroyasu,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}Shopping district chairman / President of Kobayashi Building Contractors \NKobayashi Hiroyasu
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.83,0:23:40.77,Default,T,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.77,0:23:43.34,Default,T,0,0,0,,Let me bring you some snacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.34,0:23:44.78,Default,Kobayashi,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.67,0:23:50.62,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,The tavern's getting renovated?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.62,0:23:51.89,Default,Kobayashi,0,0,0,,Well... yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.19,0:23:55.48,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Chairman, you're the president \Nof a contracting firm, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.48,0:23:58.23,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,My place needs renovation, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.23,0:24:00.73,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Can you tell me how \Nit works in some detail?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.73,0:24:02.22,Default,Kobayashi,0,0,0,,Y-Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.46,0:24:06.33,Bengoshi-Internal/Narrator,Kur,0,0,0,,Iron Spy Woman Marilyn season \N11, episode "Honey Trap."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.01,0:24:08.29,Default,Marilyn,0,0,0,,I'm a tigress.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.29,0:24:10.40,Default,Marilyn,0,0,0,,There's no man who won't fall for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.57,0:24:13.93,Default,H,0,0,0,,It appears your mother-in-law \Nis having a renovation done
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.93,0:24:17.80,Default,H,0,0,0,,by the shopping district chairman and  \Npresident of Kobayashi Building Contractors.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.80,0:24:19.16,Default,M,0,0,0,,Renovation?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.67,0:24:22.37,Bengoshi-Renovation,Letter zoom,0,0,0,,Interior Renovation Work
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.56,0:24:23.91,Default,K,0,0,0,,Miki-san, you didn't know about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.57,0:24:30.22,Default,M,0,0,0,,It's always been this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.46,0:24:33.30,Default,M,0,0,0,,Shu-chan and his mother \Nmake all the decisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.30,0:24:35.21,Default,H,0,0,0,,There's one scenario \Nthat is conceivable.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.56,0:24:38.72,Default,H,0,0,0,,The two of them are keeping\N the matter secret to you for a reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.13,0:24:44.76,Default,Y,0,0,0,,But why would they need to hide \Ntheir plan to renovate from Miki-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.52,0:24:49.57,Default,H,0,0,0,,He cheated three years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.27,0:24:52.59,Default,H,0,0,0,,The bullying started at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.96,0:24:56.50,Default,H,0,0,0,,And they've been keeping the renovation\N plan secret from Miki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.57,0:24:59.26,Default,H,0,0,0,,When you connect those \Nthree dots together...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.61,0:25:03.88,Default,K,0,0,0,,Do you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.35,0:25:05.52,Default,K,0,0,0,,her husband is in on it, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.09,0:25:09.45,Default,Y,0,0,0,,That can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.79,0:25:11.22,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,But, for what?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.92,0:25:13.75,Default,H,0,0,0,,I cannot say anything for certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.02,0:25:16.56,Default,H,0,0,0,,However, if they are \Nconspiring together...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.50,0:25:20.16,Default,H,0,0,0,,there is a high probability \Nyour husband wants a divorce.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.86,0:25:23.12,Default,H,0,0,0,,Perhaps it would be best \Nto confront him directly,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.49,0:25:25.42,Default,H,0,0,0,,and ask him yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.42,0:25:26.88,Default,K,0,0,0,,Directly?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.88,0:25:28.61,Default,K,0,0,0,,Are you sure that's a good idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.61,0:25:29.92,Default,M,0,0,0,,I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.70,0:25:32.98,Default,M,0,0,0,,I'm leaving them anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.94,0:25:35.11,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Miki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.61,0:25:37.79,Default,M,0,0,0,,Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.46,0:25:39.85,Default,M,0,0,0,,I am relying on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.63,0:25:41.78,Default,H,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.27,0:25:43.41,Default,H,0,0,0,,First off,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.41,0:25:46.65,Default,H,0,0,0,,let's see how they respond \Nto the compensation lawsuit
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.65,0:25:48.45,Default,H,0,0,0,,on grounds of bullying.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.45,0:25:49.30,Default,H,0,0,0,,On that occasion,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.30,0:25:52.86,Default,H,0,0,0,,please be careful to not \Nuse the word "divorce."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.15,0:25:57.15,Default,H,0,0,0,,Because I am going to draw \Nthat word out of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.53,0:25:59.34,Default,T,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.49,0:26:05.22,Default,H,0,0,0,,I am Hakamada Yukio of the \NHakamada Law Office.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.44,0:26:06.74,Default,H,0,0,0,,As Miki-san's legal representative,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.97,0:26:08.86,Default,H,0,0,0,,I am here to discuss a compensation lawsuit
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.86,0:26:12.48,Default,H,0,0,0,,based on your psychological abuse\N toward your daughter-in-law.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.61,0:26:14.94,Default,T,0,0,0,,Psychological abuse?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.62,0:26:17.25,Bengoshi-Hakamada_Card,Biz card,0,0,0,,Attorney at Law \NHakamada Yukio
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.47,0:26:18.59,Default,T,0,0,0,,Suing her own mother-in-law...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.02,0:26:21.94,Default,T,0,0,0,,How bad can this \Nbride's character get?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.94,0:26:25.11,Default,H,0,0,0,,I am told Miki-san has been placed \Nin charge of all household chores
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.11,0:26:27.23,Default,H,0,0,0,,after working full-time at the tavern.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.75,0:26:29.21,Default,H,0,0,0,,As a result,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.21,0:26:32.74,Default,H,0,0,0,,Miki-san has been averaging four hours of \Nsleep a night for the last three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.08,0:26:36.76,Default,H,0,0,0,,She has had no time for her \Nregular meals on a daily basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.59,0:26:40.81,Default,K,0,0,0,,This is Miki-san's health \Ndiagnosis report.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.99,0:26:44.13,Default,K,0,0,0,,As you can see from the report, \NMiki-san has incurred considerable
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.48,0:26:44.88,Bengoshi-Health_Report,Report,0,0,0,,Health diagnosis report \N\N{\b0}Name: Yoshioka Miki \N\NDiagnosis: weight loss and \Nanemia due to malnutrition. \N \NAdditional notes: Probable cause \Nof malnutrition is due to excessive\N labor and sleep deprivation \Non a daily basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.13,0:26:49.82,Default,K,0,0,0,,physical damage, including weight \Nloss and anemia due to malnutrition.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.88,0:26:46.58,Bengoshi-Health_Report,Zoom,0,0,0,,{\fs25}Health diagnosis report \N\N{\b0}Name: Yoshioka Miki \N\NDiagnosis: weight loss and anemia
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.58,0:26:48.88,Bengoshi-Health_Report,Zoom,0,0,0,,{\fs25\b0}{\a11}due to excessive labor and sleep depravation
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.36,0:26:52.92,Default,T,0,0,0,,I'm helpless.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.13,0:26:57.13,Default,T,0,0,0,,I'm getting older, and taking this kind\N of abuse from my daughter-in-law,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.13,0:26:59.09,Default,T,0,0,0,,I'm helpless.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.31,0:27:01.53,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.22,0:27:04.23,Default,T,0,0,0,,When I was married,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.23,0:27:06.70,Default,T,0,0,0,,I didn't get along with \Nmy mother-in-law, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.18,0:27:09.91,Default,T,0,0,0,,But I never would've sued her.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.45,0:27:14.07,Default,T,0,0,0,,If she doesn't like it here, \Nshe can leave any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.17,0:27:16.17,Default,H,0,0,0,,Sir,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.52,0:27:17.84,Default,H,0,0,0,,what are your thoughts on the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.26,0:27:21.67,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,She shouldn't have resorted \Nto asking a lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.66,0:27:24.07,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,We're family, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.07,0:27:26.09,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,We should talk it out like one.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.69,0:27:31.19,Default,H,0,0,0,,Miki-san has sought \Nyour help several times.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.75,0:27:36.63,Default,H,0,0,0,,But every time, you evaded her by \Nasking her to just "get along."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.11,0:27:41.61,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,All I wanted was for Miki \Nto get along with my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.15,0:27:43.03,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.38,0:27:46.91,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,If she can't, then it can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.74,0:27:50.01,Default,H,0,0,0,,Meaning?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.09,0:27:53.85,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,I will divorce Miki.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.19,0:27:57.33,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,I'm tired of all this, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.53,0:28:00.69,Default,H,0,0,0,,Miki-san does not want\N to divorce you, however.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.90,0:28:06.79,Default,H,0,0,0,,She is willing to withdraw the \Ncompensation lawsuit,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.10,0:28:10.25,Default,H,0,0,0,,on the condition that you \Nand your mother treat her fairly.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.72,0:28:12.76,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,Withdraw or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.30,0:28:17.85,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,my mother has never done anything to \Ndeserve a lawsuit in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.73,0:28:22.04,Default,K,0,0,0,,So you choose your \Nmother over Miki-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.98,0:28:26.68,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,I have only one mother, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.31,0:28:30.75,Default,T,0,0,0,,Shun-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.46,0:28:32.92,Default,H,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.41,0:28:35.24,Default,H,0,0,0,,I will relay your message to Miki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.17,0:28:38.29,Default,H,0,0,0,,The husband initiated \Nthe talk of divorce.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.64,0:28:42.59,Default,H,0,0,0,,There is no question he and his mother\N are conspiring together.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.42,0:28:45.61,Default,K,0,0,0,,Miki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.42,0:28:47.61,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.24,0:28:50.55,Default,M,0,0,0,,I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.55,0:28:52.49,Default,M,0,0,0,,I'm firm in my decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.16,0:28:55.71,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,It seems you were right \Nabout the conspiracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.20,0:28:57.27,Default,H,0,0,0,,How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.61,0:28:59.91,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I investigated as per \Nyour instructions, Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.21,0:29:01.34,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,About this girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.98,0:29:05.08,Default,M,0,0,0,,Yuriko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.64,0:29:08.46,Default,Y,0,0,0,,So this woman is your \Nhusband's ex-girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.46,0:29:13.14,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,She and Miki-san's husband have been \Nfriends since elementary school.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.14,0:29:15.79,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,They were in a relationship for nine years \Nstarting their second year in high school,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.01,0:29:17.77,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,and seven years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.77,0:29:20.82,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,a little before Miki-san \Nwould marry her husband,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.82,0:29:23.82,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Yuriko entered a marriage\N arranged by her parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.09,0:29:27.26,Default,K,0,0,0,,So, it's just as Miki-san said.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.82,0:29:29.23,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Kubo Yuriko...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.23,0:29:32.00,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,While she was married, her \Nname was Nishida Yuriko.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.81,0:29:34.24,Default,M,0,0,0,,While she "was" married?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.50,0:29:38.05,Default,Y,0,0,0,,In other words, that Yuriko \Nwoman is divorced?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.46,0:29:41.25,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,She got divorced three years ago,\N citing adultery.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.53,0:29:43.08,Default,M,0,0,0,,Three years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.08,0:29:44.21,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.21,0:29:47.82,Default,Y,0,0,0,,It was three years ago when\N Miki-san's husband cheated on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.35,0:29:53.92,Default,K,0,0,0,,Which means that his cheating\N partner must've been...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.51,0:29:55.70,Default,K,0,0,0,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.40,0:29:57.60,Default,H,0,0,0,,It is probable...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.51,0:30:00.08,Default,H,0,0,0,,that it was Kubo Yuriko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.29,0:30:06.84,Default,M,0,0,0,,It can't be true...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.10,0:30:11.81,Default,H,0,0,0,,However, based on the situation alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.81,0:30:13.93,Default,H,0,0,0,,we cannot ascertain that your husband's
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.93,0:30:17.11,Default,H,0,0,0,,cheating partner three years \Nago was Kubo Yuriko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.51,0:30:19.13,Default,Y,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.13,0:30:22.84,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Both of them were involved \Nin adultery three years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.84,0:30:24.84,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,Since she's divorced,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.84,0:30:29.70,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,it must mean that Yuriko-san \Nmust've admitted to the adultery.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.03,0:30:30.86,Default,K,0,0,0,,Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.17,0:30:34.07,Default,K,0,0,0,,Can we sue the husband for compensation,\N for having an illicit affair?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.07,0:30:36.67,Default,H,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, we cannot.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.81,0:30:38.07,Default,K,0,0,0,,You can't?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.07,0:30:39.41,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.56,0:30:43.91,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,Legally, adultery has a three-year \Nstatute of limitations.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.07,0:30:52.78,Bengoshi-Vocab_Definition1,Caption,0,0,0,,{\a2}{\fad(550,0)}Illicit activities have a three-year statute of limitations -> no compensation lawsuit
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.91,0:30:46.29,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,In other words, since \Nthree years has passed,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.29,0:30:48.72,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,he can no longer be sued \Non grounds of adultery.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.08,0:30:51.07,Bengoshi-Top,Y,0,0,0,,Only three years?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.07,0:30:53.68,Bengoshi-Top,Y,0,0,0,,I wouldn't forgive him \Nfor the rest of my life!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.99,0:30:55.35,Default,H,0,0,0,,The problem is how
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.35,0:31:00.49,Default,H,0,0,0,,we prove the husband's continued \Nrelationship with Yuriko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.08,0:31:04.71,Default,K,0,0,0,,The statute of limitations has passed,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.71,0:31:06.87,Default,K,0,0,0,,so we can't sue him for compensation...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.31,0:31:17.01,Bengoshi-Manga_Bubble,Bottom bubble,0,0,0,,She's a demon...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.01,0:31:18.84,Bengoshi-Manga_Bubble,Bubble right,0,0,0,,{\a5\3c&HC0BECC&}There's still stuff there.\NIt's a pig sty in here!\N You're really useless!\N\NI'm not your slave, Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.01,0:31:18.84,Bengoshi-Manga_Bubble,Bubble left,0,0,0,,{\a1\3c&HDFDCEA&}Even the bullying...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.36,0:31:21.25,Bengoshi-Top,Misato,0,0,0,,I would never forgive her... demon hag!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.84,0:31:20.88,Bengoshi-Credits_Left,Caption,0,0,0,,Editor at Tokiwa Publishing \NTabata Misato
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.25,0:31:22.59,Default,K,0,0,0,,Please calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.59,0:31:24.29,Default,Misato,0,0,0,,But, this mother-in-law is a demon!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.29,0:31:25.58,Default,Misato,0,0,0,,She's not human!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.58,0:31:27.03,Default,Sara,0,0,0,,May I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.60,0:31:30.89,Default,Sara,0,0,0,,Demons reside in the human heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.89,0:31:33.26,Default,Sara,0,0,0,,The world is full of demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.38,0:31:34.36,Default,Misato,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.49,0:31:35.96,Default,K,0,0,0,,It's true. Demons everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.06,0:31:40.43,Bengoshi-Credits,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}Cafe waitress \NMizutani Sara
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.20,0:31:39.71,Bengoshi-Top,Sara,0,0,0,,Your heart also has a demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.86,0:31:40.81,Bengoshi-Top,Sara,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.98,0:31:42.23,Bengoshi-Top,Sara,0,0,0,,You are a demon, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.23,0:31:42.95,Default,Misato,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.30,0:31:50.84,Default,T,0,0,0,,Looks like she'll finally \Nwant a divorce.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.09,0:31:54.99,Default,T,0,0,0,,It took three whole years. \NThat's one stubborn bride.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.20,0:31:57.08,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,The statute of limitations \Nfor adultery has passed...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.19,0:31:59.06,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,There's no way that lawyer
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.06,0:32:01.68,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,can sue for compensation, \Nnot to mention for bullying.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.68,0:32:03.82,Default,T,0,0,0,,She's the one who decided to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.82,0:32:06.19,Default,T,0,0,0,,Why should we have to pay?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.82,0:32:11.30,Default,T,0,0,0,,I was against this marriage\N from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.94,0:32:15.26,Default,T,0,0,0,,Things will go as planned, Shunsuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.28,0:32:21.10,Default,Miki,0,0,0,,This is the household's list of assets,\N in its entirety.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.57,0:32:19.94,Bengoshi-Family_Assets,Letter,0,0,0,,Yoshioka Family Assets List
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.94,0:32:25.84,Bengoshi-Family_Assets,Topics in bold,0,0,0,,{\a9}{\fs22}Real estate \N{\b0}License for tavern proprietorship \NSavings, cash \NLife insurance \NMiscellaneous properties{\b1}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.10,0:32:22.49,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.91,0:32:24.96,Default,Y,0,0,0,,All of them are in the \Nmother-in-law's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.96,0:32:27.22,Default,Y,0,0,0,,There's no joint asset \Nof husband-wife anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.22,0:32:30.97,Default,M,0,0,0,,That's because my mother-in-law \Nmanaged all the finances.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.38,0:32:33.45,Default,H,0,0,0,,We can't expect property \Ndistribution, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.45,0:32:34.55,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,This can't be happening...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.74,0:32:38.15,Default,K,0,0,0,,And the statute of \Nlimitations has passed...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.42,0:32:44.49,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.48,0:32:46.59,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I used my womanly charms
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.59,0:32:47.73,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,and enticed the blueprint out of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.73,0:32:49.10,Default,H,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.98,0:32:58.14,Default,H,0,0,0,,This is your husband and his mother's\N blueprint for renovating the tavern.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.53,0:33:00.21,Default,Y,0,0,0,,The name of the tavern is...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.84,0:33:04.92,Default,H,0,0,0,,Now we have all the \Npieces to the puzzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.53,0:33:11.79,Bengoshi-Health_Report,Blueprint,0,0,0,,{\3c&H7B91A7&}Renovation Blueprint
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.85,0:33:13.32,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Mother, in this open area here, \Ncan we install another oven?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.62,0:33:15.45,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,I want grilled items on the menu, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.45,0:33:17.67,Default,T,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.67,0:33:20.95,Default,T,0,0,0,,You can do anything \Nyou want, Yuri-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.95,0:33:22.66,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,That was quite a detour,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.66,0:33:25.06,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,but I can finally be \Nwith you, Yuri-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.06,0:33:27.40,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,I can't wait to run the place together.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.40,0:33:29.40,Default,T,0,0,0,,It's going to get busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.64,0:33:31.94,Default,T,0,0,0,,No time for coughing up lawsuits.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.94,0:33:33.92,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,Since she's married to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.92,0:33:36.40,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,we won't have to pay \Nher severance, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.63,0:33:47.28,Default,M,0,0,0,,What is the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.28,0:33:50.73,Default,T,0,0,0,,So you've finally agreed to the divorce?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.14,0:33:59.09,Default,M,0,0,0,,For seven years,\N I endeavored for this tavern.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.09,0:34:00.83,Default,M,0,0,0,,Hardly getting sleep at night,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.83,0:34:05.10,Default,M,0,0,0,,skipping meals, working, \Nand working some more.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.33,0:34:06.83,Default,M,0,0,0,,And now you do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.83,0:34:10.29,Default,T,0,0,0,,This establishment is in my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.42,0:34:12.31,Default,T,0,0,0,,You can divorce \NShunsuke or whatever,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.31,0:34:16.25,Default,T,0,0,0,,but I don't have to distribute \Na penny of my property to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.30,0:34:19.85,Default,M,0,0,0,,So, you at least accept me as his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.06,0:34:23.02,Default,M,0,0,0,,Then why are you naming \Nthe renovated tavern
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.02,0:34:26.07,Default,M,0,0,0,,after your son's illicit partner?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.66,0:34:28.06,Default,T,0,0,0,,His illicit partner's name?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.79,0:34:31.50,Bengoshi-Hakamada_Card,Blueprint,0,0,0,,{\3c&H50647F&\c&H12283D&}Dining Bar "Lily" Renovation Blueprint
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.06,0:34:31.50,Default,M,0,0,0,,Dining Bar "Lilly."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.50,0:34:33.40,Bengoshi-Hakamada_Card,Zoom,0,0,0,,{\fs30}{\3c&H50647F&\c&H12283D&}"Lily"
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.83,0:34:34.15,Default,M,0,0,0,,"Lily" is English for "Yuri." \NAs in Yuriko-san's name, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.13,0:34:37.44,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.45,0:34:41.17,Default,M,0,0,0,,I remembered the other day
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.40,0:34:44.78,Default,M,0,0,0,,when Yuriko-san came to the apartment,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.99,0:34:50.02,Default,M,0,0,0,,that it was three years ago to that day \Nthat I discovered Shun-chan was cheating.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.02,0:34:51.55,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.55,0:34:55.64,Default,M,0,0,0,,It was as if you were \Ncelebrating that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.07,0:34:57.81,Default,T,0,0,0,,Ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.81,0:35:00.03,Default,T,0,0,0,,Don't make creepy accusations.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.03,0:35:03.63,Default,H,0,0,0,,No, that day was indeed \Na day of celebration.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.04,0:35:07.99,Default,H,0,0,0,,That was the day the statute \Nof limitations passed,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.29,0:35:10.60,Default,H,0,0,0,,for the adultery between \NShunsuke-san and Yuriko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.19,0:35:15.44,Default,M,0,0,0,,I know who you had the affair with,\N three years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.68,0:35:16.97,Default,M,0,0,0,,It was Yuriko-san, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.94,0:35:19.24,Default,T,0,0,0,,Hey, you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.38,0:35:22.35,Default,T,0,0,0,,Where did you learn to \Nget bossy like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.92,0:35:26.25,Default,M,0,0,0,,Because I learned that I can't \Njust let people walk all over me.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.01,0:35:28.86,Default,Y,0,0,0,,They're not walking all over you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.26,0:35:30.99,Default,Y,0,0,0,,You stood up for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.79,0:35:37.08,Default,M,0,0,0,,Yuriko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.94,0:35:40.05,Default,M,0,0,0,,The reason for your divorce...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.86,0:35:43.33,Default,M,0,0,0,,It was because of your affair \N with him, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.95,0:35:47.30,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,Who cares?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.52,0:35:50.08,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,The statute of limitations \Nis three years for adultery.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.08,0:35:51.19,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.19,0:35:53.14,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,It's too late now!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.35,0:35:57.61,Default,Y,0,0,0,,So the three of them {\i1}were{\i0} \Ncelebrating that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.83,0:35:59.55,Default,Y,0,0,0,,And right in front of Miki-san, no less.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.55,0:36:01.82,Default,Y,0,0,0,,What disgusting people!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.63,0:36:07.44,Default,M,0,0,0,,And I believed in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.44,0:36:13.87,Default,M,0,0,0,,Even though I knew
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.53,0:36:16.84,Default,M,0,0,0,,your ex-girlfriend was always \Nin your heart, Shun-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.71,0:36:20.42,Default,M,0,0,0,,I believed that some day,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.55,0:36:25.40,Default,M,0,0,0,,you would only have eyes for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.65,0:36:30.17,Default,M,0,0,0,,So I endured Mother's bullying.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.82,0:36:34.76,Default,M,0,0,0,,I wanted to be a good wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.56,0:36:37.16,Default,M,0,0,0,,And did my best.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.16,0:36:43.28,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,I'll send you the divorce papers.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.81,0:36:45.60,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,If there's nothing else, leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.91,0:36:49.53,Default,H,0,0,0,,I may be overstepping my bounds,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.53,0:36:51.20,Default,H,0,0,0,,but there's one more \Nthing before we leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.44,0:36:53.06,Default,H,0,0,0,,Let me explain to you \Nsupplemental information
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.06,0:36:54.87,Default,H,0,0,0,,regarding the statute of \Nlimitations for adultery.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.20,0:36:56.47,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,Supplemental information?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.72,0:37:02.54,Default,H,0,0,0,,You admit that you and Yuriko-san had \Nan illicit affair three years ago, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.70,0:37:04.63,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,Yeah, I admit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.17,0:37:06.76,Default,Shun,0,0,0,,But it's past the limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.76,0:37:07.81,Default,H,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.03,0:37:11.24,Default,H,0,0,0,,There is a statute of limitations of three years\Nto sue for compensation for adultery.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.52,0:37:27.93,Bengoshi-Vocab_Word,Caption orange,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,500)}Compensation lawsuit for illicit activities
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.54,0:37:15.07,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,But that is when the \Nperpetrator is identified.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.05,0:37:27.93,Bengoshi-Vocab_Definition3,Caption white,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,500)}When the perpetrator is {\c&H933A31&\3c&HEFCCCA&}identified{\c}{\3c} → Statute of limitations of three years
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.33,0:37:16.93,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,And if the person is unidentified...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.42,0:37:27.93,Bengoshi-Vocab_Definition4,Caption red-white,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,500)}When {\c&H2925A9&\3c&HC1C6FF&}unidentified
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.93,0:37:21.46,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,the statute of limitations is three years \Nafter the person becomes identified.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.59,0:37:27.93,Bengoshi-Vocab_Definition4,Remaining caption,0,0,0,,{\a3}{\fad(500,500)}-> 3 years after identification
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.71,0:37:26.48,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,The perpetrators in this case \Nare the husband and Yuriko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.02,0:37:29.03,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,It is a fact that Miki-san knew
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.03,0:37:31.51,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,her husband was guilty of an \Nillicit affair three years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.47,0:37:37.01,Default,H,0,0,0,,Hence, we cannot sue the husband \Nfor compensation any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.68,0:37:40.79,Default,H,0,0,0,,However, there is one more perpetrator.\N The illicit partner in the adultery.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.79,0:37:42.01,Default,H,0,0,0,,That would be Yuriko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.01,0:37:44.41,Default,H,0,0,0,,Miki-san found out that it was her,\N today, for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.65,0:37:47.14,Default,H,0,0,0,,Hence, within the next three years...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.54,0:37:52.49,Default,H,0,0,0,,Yuriko-san can be sued \Nfor compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.09,0:37:57.21,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Hey, Shunsuke, this isn't\N how you said it'd go!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.21,0:37:59.86,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Why do{\i1} I {\i0}have to get \Nsued for compensation?!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.86,0:38:01.18,Default,T,0,0,0,,Calm down. Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.18,0:38:01.90,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,And you too, Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.90,0:38:03.83,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,I did this because you promised \Nyou'd chase that wife out!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.69,0:38:06.45,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,I waited three years \Nto be with Shunsuke,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.45,0:38:08.41,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,and this is what I get?!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.59,0:38:09.77,Default,T,0,0,0,,Zip it, be quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.98,0:38:10.91,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,I've had it!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.46,0:38:13.15,Default,T,0,0,0,,Yuri! Yuri-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.59,0:38:18.92,Default,H,0,0,0,,Yuriko-san was waiting for \NMiki-san to leave, she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.40,0:38:23.46,Default,H,0,0,0,,Which means the husband and Yuriko-san's \Nadulterous affair continued until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.61,0:38:28.48,Default,H,0,0,0,,That means the statute of limitations\Nto sue for compensation
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.48,0:38:30.46,Default,H,0,0,0,,has not yet expired.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.88,0:38:33.58,Default,T,0,0,0,,Don't be ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.95,0:38:36.94,Default,T,0,0,0,,I can finally renovate \Nthis establishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.94,0:38:39.10,Default,T,0,0,0,,I have no money to pay \Nfor compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.95,0:38:41.03,Default,H,0,0,0,,Tomoe-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.48,0:38:43.84,Default,H,0,0,0,,You were going to renovate the place \Ninto a European-style restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.11,0:38:46.77,Default,H,0,0,0,,You were going to name it "Lily," \Nin reference to Yuriko-san's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.09,0:38:50.89,Default,H,0,0,0,,Thus, in order to drive Miki-san\N to file for divorce of her own accord,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.89,0:38:53.47,Default,H,0,0,0,,you continually bullied \Nher for three whole years.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.47,0:38:57.22,Default,T,0,0,0,,Shunsuke and Yuri-chan are \Ndestined to be married.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.62,0:39:01.86,Default,T,0,0,0,,But, he had to marry \Nthat bride there instead!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.36,0:39:04.09,Default,H,0,0,0,,Again, I may be overstepping my bounds,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.12,0:39:06.92,Default,H,0,0,0,,but the mother-in-law \Nconspired with her son,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.92,0:39:08.10,Default,H,0,0,0,,planned on driving out his wife and
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.10,0:39:11.13,Default,H,0,0,0,,getting her son hitched \Nto his illicit partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.46,0:39:13.75,Default,H,0,0,0,,Which means you are guilty \Nof a joint unlawful act.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.19,0:39:17.74,Default,H,0,0,0,,Hence it is possible for Miki-san \Nto sue you, the mother-in-law,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.74,0:39:19.97,Default,H,0,0,0,,for compensation as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.12,0:39:22.98,Default,T,0,0,0,,This can't be happening...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.60,0:39:39.56,Default,T,0,0,0,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.01,0:40:08.08,Default,K,0,0,0,,Yoshie-san, you're in high spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.08,0:40:10.56,Default,Y,0,0,0,,The place has a new owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.56,0:40:11.81,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Guess who it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.00,0:40:13.32,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.32,0:40:14.19,Default,K,0,0,0,,Miki-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.30,0:40:17.58,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Thanks to the triple compensation \Nfrom husband, his lover, and mother-in-law,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.58,0:40:19.13,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Miki-san is now the official owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.13,0:40:22.20,Default,Y,0,0,0,,And today's opening day!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.91,0:40:24.99,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Why don't we all go for a drink there?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.99,0:40:27.67,Default,Y,0,0,0,,She gave me vouchers, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.67,0:40:29.98,Bengoshi-Coupon,Voucher,0,0,0,,Restaurant {\fs25}Miki{\fs} \N{\c&H1B41D5&}10%{\c} off voucher
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.01,0:40:28.53,Default,Y,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.53,0:40:29.98,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,Wow, look at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.98,0:40:32.54,Default,K,0,0,0,,How wonderful for Miki-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.54,0:40:33.52,Bengoshi-Top,Y,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.52,0:40:35.54,Bengoshi-Top,Y,0,0,0,,I'm going to drink until I puke tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.54,0:40:37.27,Bengoshi-Top,Rina,0,0,0,,Please, count me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.27,0:40:39.33,Bengoshi-Top,K,0,0,0,,I told you, I don't drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.33,0:40:40.68,Bengoshi-Top,Y,0,0,0,,Both of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.68,0:40:42.74,Bengoshi-Top,Y,0,0,0,,how cold can you get?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.74,0:40:45.30,Bengoshi-Top,Y,0,0,0,,Don't you want to go and \Nsupport her establishment?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.30,0:40:46.79,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,Regarding that,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.79,0:40:49.69,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,as a main point of \Nattraction on her menu,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.69,0:40:51.93,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,I invented a bread that \Nwill go well with liquor.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.06,0:40:56.10,Bengoshi-Top,Y,0,0,0,,What's that got to do with \Nsupporting her establishment?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.10,0:40:58.74,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,Because it's a main point \Nof attraction on the menu.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.74,0:41:00.68,Bengoshi-Top,K,0,0,0,,I'm getting the chills.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.68,0:41:01.94,Bengoshi-Top,K,0,0,0,,I'm getting bad vibes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.94,0:41:04.34,Bengoshi-Top,Rina,0,0,0,,What's this numb deja-vu?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.84,0:41:05.84,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,Here they come.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.52,0:41:09.08,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,The perfect complement to shochu,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.08,0:41:10.21,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,pickled-plum bread!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.86,0:41:11.48,Bengoshi-Top,Y,0,0,0,,Fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.48,0:41:13.58,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,For Japanese rice wine, \Nsalt-pickled squid bread!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.75,0:41:14.49,Bengoshi-Top,Y,0,0,0,,Fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.49,0:41:15.90,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,And one more added bonus,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.90,0:41:16.65,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,green-pea-soup bread!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.65,0:41:17.79,Bengoshi-Top,Y,0,0,0,,Fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.95,0:41:19.24,Bengoshi-Top,Rina,0,0,0,,Let's go there on our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.24,0:41:19.66,Bengoshi-Top,K,0,0,0,,Let's.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.66,0:41:21.89,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,And this goes well with beer...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.15,0:41:23.17,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,black-beer bread!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.17,0:41:24.12,Bengoshi-Top,Y,0,0,0,,Fail!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.31,0:41:26.93,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,Oh wait, there's one more.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.23,0:41:29.03,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,How about this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.25,0:41:31.41,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,A friendly companion \Nto sodas... soda bread!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.41,0:41:32.64,Bengoshi-Top,Y,0,0,0,,The sales pitch is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.79,0:41:33.96,Bengoshi-Top,Y,0,0,0,,Fail!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.53,0:41:38.02,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,All of them failed...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.58,0:41:41.48,Bengoshi-Final_Battle,Caption,0,0,0,,The Divorce Chaser's Final Battle
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.48,0:41:45.82,Bengoshi-End_Splash1,Caption,0,0,0,,The client is {\c&H73FF76&}Kanae's ex-husband!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.59,0:41:43.38,Bengoshi-Top,Yoshihito,0,0,0,,We're being sued \Nfor compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.38,0:41:45.82,Bengoshi-Top,Yoshihito,0,0,0,,My wife, Shiori, \Nwas caught cheating.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.82,0:41:49.35,Bengoshi-Top,Yoshihito,0,0,0,,I am Honjo Yayoi-san's legal \Nrepresentative, Karasuma Keiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.85,0:41:55.93,Bengoshi-End_Splash2,Caption,0,0,0,,The opponent is a formidable lawyer. Hakamada's {\c&HB337BB&}ex-lover!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.35,0:41:51.63,Bengoshi-Top,Y,0,0,0,,She's Hakamada-sensei's ex-lover.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.63,0:41:55.33,Bengoshi-Top,Y,0,0,0,,Hakamada-sensei was falsely accused \Nof stalking ten years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.33,0:41:56.93,Bengoshi-Top,Y,0,0,0,,and was fired from the law firm.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.93,0:41:59.00,Bengoshi-Top,Y,0,0,0,,She used Hakamada-sensei \Nas a stepping stone
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.00,0:42:01.23,Bengoshi-Top,Y,0,0,0,,to get promoted at the law firm.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.83,0:42:04.63,Bengoshi-End_Splash1,Caption,0,0,0,,{\c&H1DCEB8&}A dramatic past is revealed
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.23,0:42:05.82,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,There's no lawyer who can surpass \Nher ability to garner information.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.70,0:42:09.47,Bengoshi-Fiction,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(230,0)}This drama is a work of fiction
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.82,0:42:06.57,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,So for this particular case,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.57,0:42:09.44,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,I think you should consult \Na different lawyer.
